alaRipngUpdateInterval.name: alaRipngUpdateInterval
alaRipngUpdateInterval.description: Interval (in seconds) that RIPng routing updates will be sent out. The value must be less than or equal to one-third the the invalid timer and greater or equal to two times the jitter value.

alaRipngInvalidTimer.name: alaRipngInvalidTimer
alaRipngInvalidTimer.description: Time in seconds that a route will remain active in RIB before being moved to the invalid state. The value must be at least three times the update interval. The defined range of 1 to 360 allows backwards compatibility with older devices which do not enforce the three-times constraint. For newer devices which enforce the three-times constraint with the update interval, the minimum allowed value of the invalid timer is 3.

alaRipngHolddownTimer.name: alaRipngHolddownTimer

alaRipngGarbageTimer.name: alaRipngGarbageTimer
alaRipngGarbageTimer.description: Time to keep a route before garbage collection.

alaRipngRouteCount.name: alaRipngRouteCount
alaRipngRouteCount.description: The number of network routes in RIPng routing table.

alaRipngGlobalRouteTag.name: alaRipngGlobalRouteTag
alaRipngGlobalRouteTag.description: The route tag that will be added to all RIPng entries

alaRipngTriggeredSends.name: alaRipngTriggeredSends
alaRipngTriggeredSends.description: Controls whether trigged updates contain entire RIB or just changes.

alaRipngJitter.name: alaRipngJitter
alaRipngJitter.description: Jitter to use when sending updates. The value must be less than one-half the update interval.
